Step 1: Start EC2
Step 2: Connect to EC2
Step 3: Start Jenkins
Step 4: 




To DELETE deployments:

------------------------------------------For AWS----------------------------------------------------------
1. login to AWS:
2. run $aws eks --region eu-west1 update-kubeconfig --name x23183209-multicloud
3. $kubectl get deployments
4. $kubectl delete deployment simple-app-deployment
5. $aws eks update-kubeconfig --region eu-west1 --name x23183209-multicloud
6. $kubectl scale deployment x23183209-multicloud --replicas=0

------------------------------------------For GCP----------------------------------------------------------

1. login to GCP:
2. run $gcloud container clusters get-credentials gcp-multicloud --zone europe-west1-b --project elegant-hope-441319-t6
3. $kubectl get deployments
4. $kubectl delete deployment simple-app-deployment

------------------------------------------For Azure--------------------------------------------------------
1. Login to Azure
2. $run az aks get-credentials --resource-group Multicloud --name multicloudAKS
3. $kubectl get deployments
4. $kubectl delete deployment simple-app-deployment

